gurmukhi: swgr mQq jYsy inksy AMmiRq ibKu praupkwr n ibkwr smsir hY
transliteration: Saagar Madat Jaisay Nikasay Anmrit Bikhu , Paraoupakaar N Bikaar Samasari Hai ?
translation: Churning of ocean produced nectar and poison. Despite coming out of the same ocean, the goodness of nectar and harm of poison is not the same.

gurmukhi: ibKu Acvq hoq rqn ibnws kwl Acey AMmiRq mUey jIvq Amr hY
transliteration: Bikhu Achavat Hot Ratan Binaas Kaala , Achaay Anmrit Mooay Jeevat Amar Hai ?
translation: Poison ends the jewel-like life whereas nectar resuscitates or revives the dead making him immortal.

gurmukhi: jYsy qwro qwrI eyk lost sY pRgt huie bMD moK pdvI sMswr ibsQr hY
transliteration: Jaisay Taaro Taaree Ayk Losat Sai Pragat Hui , Bandh Mokh Padavee Sansaar Bisadar Hai ?
translation: As the key and the lock are made of the same metal, but a lock results in bondage whereas a key frees the bonds.

gurmukhi: qYsy hI AswD swD sn Aau mjIT giq gurmiq durmiq tyvsY n tr hY ]162]
transliteration: Taisay Hee Asaadh Saadh San Au Majeetth Gati , Gurmati Duramati Tayvasai N Tar Hai ?162?
translation: Similarly a man does not give up his base wisdom but a person of Godly disposition never falters from the wisdom and teachings of the Guru. (162)
